File: platform/mcp-server/src/state.ts, lines 329-335. Object.freeze is shallow — the Maps and array inside EMPTY_REGISTRY are still mutable. Fix: freeze each inner collection before freezing the outer object. E.g.:

const plugins = new Map(); Object.freeze(plugins);
... repeat for toolLookup, resourceLookup, promptLookup, failures ...
export const EMPTY_REGISTRY: PluginRegistry = Object.freeze({ plugins, toolLookup, ... });

Note: Object.freeze on a Map prevents adding properties to the Map object but does NOT prevent .set() in all engines. To truly prevent mutation, you may need to override .set/.delete to throw, or simply document that the freeze is for the outer shape. Check if Map.prototype.set respects Object.freeze in Node.js 22 — if it does, freezing alone is sufficient. If not, wrap the maps in a Proxy or use Object.defineProperty to make them non-writable on the parent object (they already are via Object.freeze on the parent).
